---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Patrons — Telecine"
  description="Telecine is free to watch and always will be. Patronage keeps the transmitter warm and the programming ambitious."
>
  <article class="wrap">
    <h1 class="page-title">Patrons</h1>
    <p class="page-lede">
      The network is free to watch, and that is permanent. Patronage is how it grows.
    </p>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Telecine costs almost nothing to run — that is the elegance of the design — but programming
        is labour: finding the best surviving print of each film, verifying it, writing the notes,
        composing seasons that mean something. Patronage funds that labour, the way membership funds
        a film society. Not a paywall in front of the films (they belong to you already), but a way
        to stand behind the projector.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tiers">
      <section class="tier" data-settle="0">
        <h2 class="tier-name">The Viewer</h2>
        <p class="tier-price"><span class="stamp">Free · forever</span></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Every channel, every film, always on</li>
          <li>The Guide, the programme notes, the whole set</li>
          <li>No account. No tracking. Just tune in.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="tier featured" data-settle="90">
        <div class="bars" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
        <h2 class="tier-name">Founding Patron</h2>
        <p class="tier-price"><span class="stamp">Opens with Season Two</span></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your name in the network's end-of-night credit roll (or your anonymity, kept)</li>
          <li>The printed seasonal programme — the guide as a physical object worth keeping</li>
          <li>A programming vote each season: one film on one channel is the patrons' pick</li>
          <li>First tune-in when new channels test their signal</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="tier" data-settle="180">
        <h2 class="tier-name">The Affiliate</h2>
        <p class="tier-price"><span class="stamp">For cinemas &amp; societies</span></p>
        <ul>
          <li>A Transmission of your own: a channel programmed for your venue, festival, or society</li>
          <li>Programme notes written to hang beside your screenings</li>
          <li>The broadcast engine, pointed at your audience</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Founding memberships open with Season Two, once the network has earned the ask. Until then
        the best ways to back the transmitter: <a href="https://github.com/brunohart/telecine">star
        or contribute to the source</a>, tell exactly one person who would love CH 02, and
        <a href="https://archive.org/donate">give to the Internet Archive</a>, whose shelves this
        network is built on.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  article.wrap { position: relative; }
  .tiers { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1.6rem; margin: 2.4rem 0; }
  .tier { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; background: var(--card); padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.7rem; }
  .tier.featured { border-color: var(--line-strong); padding-top: 0; }
  .tier.featured .bars { margin: 0 -1.5rem 1.4rem; border-radius: 6px 6px 0 0; overflow: hidden; }
  .tier-name { font-size: 1.35rem; }
  .tier-price { margin: 0.3rem 0 1rem; color: var(--signal-deep); }
  .tier ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; display: grid; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .prose { max-width: 66ch; }
</style>
